<br>
My gut based on these forums is that they have made the PoP pets with the epic as a model, and raised the level appropriately. This will have (in my opinion) the nice effect of gently superceding the epic over time as you move through the 60s. <br>
<br>
The Epic is after all a monster. It is head and shoulders above the pther pets for the level at which it is acquirable. It is sensible then to maintain pet progressionfor the new pets to be a step above the epic without being another Epic-style jump.<br>
<br>
Planar Pets &gt; Epic &gt; Greater Vocerates is an entirely appropriate transition in my opinion, the epic remains a serious goal for those getting through and approaching the 50s, with it for a very long period of time you will have a very strong pet. By attaining the epic pet, the young Master of the Elements gains a significant &quot;leap frog&quot; of pet power, literally pushing the bounds of mortal magic and gaining a huge boon for getting through the 50s and early 60s.<br>
<br>
The epic itself however is of mortal Norrathian magic. Certainly, the pet is indeed powerful, and the Master of the Elements was duly impressed that we were able to find the balance to complete the arduous quest. However:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You say, 'Hail, Master of Elements'<br>
<br>
Master of Elements says 'I... am... the... Master... of... Elements.. Elements... Forgive... me. I am... unaccustomed.. to.. speaking.. this.. mortal... tongue. Might.. you... be... the... One? <br>
<br>
You say, 'This mortal is the one'<br>
<br>
Master of Elements says 'Trilith... Magi'kot.. knelt.. before.. the.. orb.. in.. his.. his.. last.. few.. moments... of.. mortal.. life. He... too... believed.. that.. he.. had.. the.. power.. and.. balance.. needed.. to.. grasp... control.. of.. the.. elements. He.. was.... flawed. Coming.. to... me... is.. a.. matter.. of.. no.. small.. import. Only.. only... one.. who.. is.. of.. balance.. and.. power... power.. may.. control.. the.. Orb.. of... Mastery. Give.... give.. me.. the.. Elements.. you.. have... gathered.. and.. I.. shall.. see.. if.. you.. are.. ready.. ready.. to control.. the... Elements.. of... life.. life.. life. <br>
<br>
Master of Elements says 'You... are.. balanced... and.. powerful.. for.. a.. mortal... Hogfather ..... Hogfather . <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>More.. so.. than.... Magi'kot. But.... you.. are.. not.. yet.. ready.. to.. transcend.. transcend... this.. mortal.. coil. Take.. take.. seize.. this.. Orb... for.. you.. are.. worthy.. of.. reward.. and.. with... the.. aid.. of... the... balance.. balance.. contained.. within.. the.. Orb.. you.. may.. yet.. reach.. the... ultimate... Mastery.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
(sort of in character here bear with me)<br>
<br>
I believe that the Master of the Elements, duly impressed with the efforts of the mortal magician, grants the quester the ability to summon a creature of the Planes themselves, cast into a mortal shell. This creature is indeed a true power when then taken back into the mortal realms.<br>
<br>
But we have grown now. The knowledge of the Planes themselves, and how to bind the minions of the Planes, is coming to us through the work of the Elders. The companions we now call to do our bidding are hence no longer forced to work within the restrictions of a mortal body. The Planar elementals are the result of this work.<br>
<br>
Will the Elders studying the Orb of Mastery itself be able to discern how to fashion a weapon capable of casting the essence of the Epic Pet into a form not limited by these restrictions of mortality?<br>
<br>
What would such a creature be like? Who could command a beast of the like? I personally eagerly await the outcome of this research and hopefully it will bear fruit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirellyn@themagicianstower>Sirellyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 3:04:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7706.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ..</span><hr size=1> So far only seen water pet level 62..   <br>
