<br>
The orb came from the planes. The orb is what holds the magical energy from the planes so that we can manifest elements.  Either way from a rolling playing perspective or from a realist perspective your argument has flaws. However I am going to take the realist approach.<br>
<br>
Wizard Epic - Hmmm mobs level 63 and above still have to fight through that rune to get to the wizard. Do they have a better post 60 rune? Yes they do. Do they have to put away there epic rune when they fight 63+ mobs in the planes? No? Kinda makes you wonder why these planes mobs which are so smart can't get past a old world rune huh?<br>
<br>
Druid/Necro/Shaman Epics - Hmmm seems these new smart planes mobs can't resist that old school Norathian magic. All three of these classes are using there epics to solo just find and /gasp they land on lvl 63 and above mobs even tho they have spells that are better.  Also extended affliction works on these epics, yet improved damage doesn't work on right clicks /boggle.<br>
<br>
Melee epics<br>
<br>
Hmm I haven't noticed a mob yet that resist a old world melee epic. I saw a rogue crit backstab with a Ragebringer made from Norathian magic. Seems odd that these new planar mobs about level 63 can't resist those epics. Also these old epics do more damage do to high skill caps and aa via the planes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now we move to the mage. Our epic is the only one that we have to put away when fighting lvl 63 and above mobs. I am not asking that epic be improved in max hit ect..just that the level is raised so that it can hit lvl 63+ mobs.  I am being realistic. The mage epic is a bitch to do and alot of time goes into getting it. It shouldn't be made useless vs. 63+ mobs when NO OTHER EPIC IN THE GAME IS! I could deal with it before because the average experience mob wasn't 60+, but now that is the norm it is time for the epic to be raised in level.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 673<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 5:33:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7706.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/photo.gif width=90 height=112></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Our Epic is also the only one that is unique in that it calls forth a pet rather than having an effect that does something. This is the central crux of the matter, and its always going to come down to a personal choice.<br>
<br>
I want to replace my Epic pet. I haven't had it long, but I don't want it to be the best in the game anymore. I am looking forward to trying out the new pets and being ecstatic the first time my new Water pet assassinates something and everyone around me goes &quot;OMG&quot;.<br>
<br>
I want to have to choose which pet I will take into battle with me instead of just clicking on my epic stick.<br>
<br>
If the epics were made so that they stay the best in the game forever, then getting it would mean &quot;winning&quot; the game in that respect. Perhaps VI made a criticasl flaw in making the Mage Epic summon the best pet in the game for the past two years, because the choice of replacing that pet, or introducing useless pet spells for those who have it was never going to be an easy one, and would never make everyone happy.<br>
<br>
No other epic has an ability that superceded a spell line totally. The argument for and against making the epic the best is one with valid points on either side. I want to have new useful pets, not spells added straight to the back of my spellbook.<br>
<br>
IMHO a better solution is to just bite the bullet and change the epic so that it casts a spell that gives any pet the epic proc, and acts as a powerful focus item, slightly less good than the VT gloves. Yep, its a nerf to many with the epic, depending on your level, but would correct a glaring problem with the whole quest. Perhaps there could be some way of doing this voluntarily.<br>
<br>
